snippet.title: Pray for Israel - Barron Trump Sings
snippet.description:
Pray for Israel

Check us out on Spotify! https://open.spotify.com/album/3y1CZVxPBVqYl2ljdNVWno?si=lLRWLYbeQcuXD9TQDeKi7A

⬇️⬇️⬇️ Watch more videos below! ⬇️⬇️⬇️
https://youtu.be/WBHJZs8ZeFQ
https://youtu.be/GAdihLnAiXk
https://youtu.be/SZZW8YMZlMg?si=kP7ZE5s5fhhjjpX2
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=hq_JjAodbY0
[Verse 1]
I’ve seen the headlines, I’ve watched the pain
A land of promise crying in the rain
Ancient walls still stand so tall
But hearts are breaking behind them all

They fight for peace but walk through fire
Still holding tight to a dream much higher
A chosen land, a sacred name
But still the world don’t treat it the same

[Chorus]
So pray for Israel, pray tonight
For every mother who holds her child tight
For the soldier standing in the holy dust
And the faith that still says, “In God we trust”
Lift your voice, don't be afraid
Call on Heaven, call His name
In these dark and heavy days
We need to pray, we need to pray for Israel

[Verse 2]
I’ve heard the stories, I’ve read the Book
Where giants fell and courage shook
Where prophets walked, where Jesus cried
Where truth was nailed but never died

From Tel Aviv to Galilee
This fight is more than what we see
It’s light and dark, it’s wrong and right
It’s history calling us to rise and fight

[Chorus]
So pray for Israel, pray tonight
For the homes that vanish in the night
For the fathers lost in endless war
Still believing in something more
Don’t stay silent, don’t look away
The world needs strength, the world needs faith
In these final, trying days
We need to pray, we need to pray for Israel

[Bridge]
This isn’t politics, this is prophecy
It’s not about sides, it’s destiny
We stand with truth, we stand with grace
We lift them up, the chosen race

[Chorus – Final]
Yeah, pray for Israel, lift that flame
Let every nation know His name
From the White House to the Western Wall
God is watching over all
Stand for hope, stand for peace
Let mercy and justice never cease
This is the call of our day
We need to pray, we must pray for Israel

[Outro]
I may be young, but I know what's right
And I won't stop praying through the night
Lord, bless the land where Your promise stays
We need to pray… we need to pray for Israel
